        high: 'Stuck states post-practice can range from mildly elevated awareness to persistent depersonalization or dissociation. They are particularly common after long retreats and can persist for days to weeks. Re-integration practices (movement, embodied activity, social engagement, ordinary tasks) are first-line responses; persistent stuckness deserves clinical attention.'
