        high: 'Visual phenomena are well documented in contemplative practice and are usually benign manifestations of relaxed cortical states (similar to hypnagogic phenomena at sleep onset). They can include phosphenes, color flashes, geometric patterns (form constants), and complex imagery. Distinction is important when they include sustained hallucinations, voices, or content that distresses or convinces the practitioner of unusual reality (e.g., believing the visions are messages from outside).'
